set of resources. While a user in team 1 may not be able to see the details of other teams dataflow, it is still important that users in team 1 can see when back pressure or very large queues exist in other teams groups since that can ultimately have an impact on their dataflows. Team 1 user will not be able to see the actual data just queue counts.\r\n\r\n3. Sometimes their are multiple team dataflows that share the same source data. For example and ConsumeKafka processor that feeds \"success\" relationship multiple times int to different teams dataflows. If we hide components completely, how would we render these other success relationships? If we just hide them as well, the source processor would appear as only having one outbound connection. This would make it impossible for team1 to troubleshoot id ConsumeKafka just stopped consuming because one of these non visible connections.\r\n\r\n\r\nThis is the updated question URL:-https://community.hortonworks.com/questions/115771/nifi-hide-flows.html\r\n\r\nPushing the ticket to resolved status. Verified by Vijay on the same.\r\n\r\nRegads,\r\n-Pramod.\r\n','2017-10-11 08:51:45',0),(767,414,'Issue',26,'Hi All,\r\n          COnfigured the jobs in jenkins for below projects and added web hooks in bitbucket  to trigger jobs of project when devlooper pushed the code to bitbucket.\r\n\r\n1.TenantManagementApp.\r\n2.SocketServer.\r\n3.EntityMaker.\r\n4.EntityActor.\r\n\r\nTwo jobs created for the above project for build and publish to local Service Fabric.here i have attached screenshot of jenkins job i have created \r\n\r\nRegards,\r\n-Pramod \r\n','2017-10-11 08:58:15',0),(768,494,'Issue',56,'','2017-10-11 09:00:53',0),(769,474,'Issue',64,'','2017-10-11 10:25:24',0),(770,229,'Issue',26,'','2017-10-11 10:25:45',0),(771,238,'Issue',50,'Hi All,\r\n\r\nAdding document for Service Fabric with architecture in the document. Have explained what services we will be using as well. \r\nI will be making changes if required. Adding th